Frequently Asked Questions for NRG Energy (NYSE:NRG)
What is NRG Energy's stock symbol?

NRG Energy trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "NRG."



How often does NRG Energy pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for NRG Energy?

NRG Energy announced a quarterly dividend on Thursday, July 20th. Shareholders of record on Tuesday, August 1st will be paid a dividend of $0.03 per share on Tuesday, August 15th. This represents a $0.12 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 0.47%. The ex-dividend date is Friday, July 28th.  View NRG Energy's Dividend History.



How were NRG Energy's earnings last quarter?

NRG Energy, Inc. (NYSE:NRG) issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May, 2nd. The company reported ($0.52) EPS for the quarter, missing the Zacks' consensus estimate of ($0.41) by $0.11. The company earned $2.76 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.29 billion. NRG Energy had a positive return on equity of 7.01% and a negative net margin of 7.81%.  View NRG Energy's Earnings History.



Where is NRG Energy's stock going? Where will NRG Energy's stock price be in 2017?

7 brokers have issued 12 month price objectives for NRG Energy's shares. Their predictions range from $12.00 to $27.00. On average, they expect NRG Energy's stock price to reach $21.83 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for NRG Energy.



What are analysts saying about NRG Energy stock?

Here are some recent quotes from research analysts about NRG Energy stock: 
1. According to Zacks Investment Research, "NRG Energy is gaining from its asset drop-down program that is in sync with its long- term growth strategy. Its cost saving measures, providing power to a wide variety of customers, debt reduction plans and expansion of renewable operations should further drive growth. Since the company does not depend on a single customer to generate revenues, migration of customers to other operators does nothave anysignificant impact on the company’s earnings. Shares of NRG Energy have returned more than the broader industry in the last six months. However, stringent environmental regulations, restructuring of GenOn, fluctuating weather conditions and intense competition in the wholesale power markets are headwinds." (7/11/2017)
2. UBS AG analysts commented, "Following our latest mgmt. meetings, we are formally rolling forward our price target to reflect the reduction of the entire unallocated corporate SG&A budget of $140 Mn as part of the first stage of cost cutting reduction targets. While this appears achievable, it appears likely below Street expectations of well north of $300 Mn+. We see only a slight positive skew to shares, particularly with more challenging macro datapoints including nascent concerns on HY turnaround (more neg for DYN)." (3/20/2017)




Who are some of NRG Energy's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to NRG Energy include Sse Plc (SSE), FirstEnergy Corporation (FE), Entergy Corporation (ETR), Enersis Americas S.A. (ENIA), Pinnacle West Capital Corporation (PNW), Alliant Energy Corporation (LNT), Scana Corporation (SCG), CPFL Energia S.A. (CPL), The AES Corporation (AES), Westar Energy (WR), OGE Energy Corporation (OGE), Pepco Holdings LLC (POM), Empresa Nacional de Electricidad S.A. (EOCC), Great Plains Energy (GXP), Calpine Corporation (CPN), IDACORP (IDA), Pampa Energia S.A. (PAM) and Portland General Electric Company (POR).



